&lt;img src="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/wp-imports/art/demo_magnid.png" alt="">&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Twitch emoticons I&amp;rsquo;ve been working on today to submit to Kripp.  Any feedback is appreciated.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="khadgar">Khadgar&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Hero Khadgar, looking intrigued/disgusted. Could be fun for Subs to cheer on a class, cheer for an arena pick, or express the mentioned emotions.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="magni">Magni&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Hero Magni I think could be fun to express surprise/excitement/happiness. Again, could be used to cheer or jeer the warrior class as well.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="topdeck">TopDeck&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Thought it would be fun to express hate, surprise, or cheer for Top decking.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>BaseTradeTV Reflection</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/esports/basetradetv-reflection/</link><pubDate>Thu, 26 Jun 2014 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/esports/basetradetv-reflection/</guid><description>&lt;p>Though I am mired in my current work, I find that it can be a good thing to take small breaks from the grind to reignite my passion for artistic work by tackling smaller more focused projects.  I enjoy doing overlay and eSports work for many reasons, but one of the them is that it utilizes a generally very simple concepts that can be deeply explored through creative problem solving and intelligent design.  This allows me to push aside a lot of the extra considerations that can weigh down exploration of design while I’m working on such a complicated project as my Indie game Mecromage.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>SC2Pro Stream Front</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/esports/sc2pro-stream-front/</link><pubDate>Tue, 30 Oct 2012 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/esports/sc2pro-stream-front/</guid><description>&lt;p>I was commissioned to do a budget web splash page.  The purpose -to have a stream front that fans can navigate to and see multiple streams simultaneously in action, from a given team or group.  The challenge - to create a design in three hours.  While I accomplished the initial three hours concept goal, I did spend another three refining some of the ideas.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;a href="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/64a19c4a99e7_8817/sc2prostreamsC03.jpg">&lt;img src="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/64a19c4a99e7_8817/sc2prostreamsC03_thumb.jpg" alt="sc2prostreamsC03" title="sc2prostreamsC03">&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>FOUR STREAMS ACTIVE – OFFLINE TAB DOWN&lt;/strong>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Team Eve Gaming Logo</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/team-eve-gaming-logo/</link><pubDate>Thu, 31 May 2012 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/team-eve-gaming-logo/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/eve_logo_large.png">&lt;img src="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/eve_logo_large.png" alt="eve_logo_large" title="eve_logo_large">&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Creating Team Eve’s logo was a rewarding experience, and a test of the process of achieving a shared vision with a client.  Below I discuss the process I used to communicate online, across the globe, to deliver not only a logo for an up and coming eSports team, but some working assets for their web and streaming needs.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>PHASE 1 - INTENT&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;hr>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/wp-imports/gamedev/1.png" alt="1">&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Establish Intent - The above image compiled the sources that I asked the client bring to me as direction on how we might evaluate their personal tastes for their design and their intent.  I want the final product to represent as best as possible the client&amp;rsquo;s unique identity as well as resolve their professional needs.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Grubby Splash Protoss Video Player</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/esports/grubby-splash-protoss-video-player/</link><pubDate>Wed, 11 Jan 2012 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/esports/grubby-splash-protoss-video-player/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/splash_page_demo_04.jpg">&lt;img src="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/splash_page_demo_04.jpg" alt="splash_page_demo_04" title="splash_page_demo_04">&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>A web page splash page for a the work in progress FollowGrubby.com.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>I originally took in game screen-shots to construct an image that would serve as backdrop for Grubby’s announcement to his fans.  Wanting to add more personality, I decided to illustrate my own Protoss UI over the top of the draft, and it came out much better than I had anticipated.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>In the end, I actually also created the .html css file for the live splash page.  It took a little bit of learning on top of what I already know, but after about 30 minutes I had the file that would go live. I was quite proud of myself.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Downwhere’s Man</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/illustration/downwheres-man/</link><pubDate>Wed, 19 Oct 2011 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/illustration/downwheres-man/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/1a4b0886043f_11DA0/manshizzle_wallpaper_16-10.jpg">&lt;img src="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/1a4b0886043f_11DA0/manshizzle_wallpaper_16-10_thumb.jpg" alt="manshizzle_wallpaper_16-10" title="manshizzle_wallpaper_16-10">&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>A friend of mine from the WCR community has been hard at work on creating a series of hilarious videos where he takes games that allow you to make morality decisions and plays out the meanest of the options. He commentates over the gaming for added entertainment.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>So far Manshizzle, the the selfish antihero and star of the series has found himself guzzling glory in Mass Effect, Dragon Age, and Fallout. Feel free to be entertained at his youtube channel: &lt;a href="http://www.youtube.com/downwhere">youtube/downwhere&lt;/a> (WARNING, Manshizzle’s exploits are the polar opposite of a G rating.)&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Grubby Shop Coming Soon</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/esports/grubby-shop-coming-soon/</link><pubDate>Wed, 31 Aug 2011 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/esports/grubby-shop-coming-soon/</guid><description>&lt;p>While in the process of designing Grubby’s first run website, we decided the Shop would need a place holder as we were to release before it was ready.  I took the opportunity to have a little fun &lt;img src="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/Grubby-Shop-Coming-Soon_9031/wlEmoticon-openmouthedsmile.png" alt="Open-mouthed smile">&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;a href="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/Grubby-Shop-Coming-Soon_9031/shop_coming_soon2-copy.png">&lt;img src="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/Grubby-Shop-Coming-Soon_9031/shop_coming_soon2-copy_thumb.png" alt="shop_coming_soon2 copy" title="shop_coming_soon2 copy">&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The Stacraft 2 SCV has his work cut out for him.  This looks to be a long build time.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/shop_coming_soon.png">&lt;img src="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/shop_coming_soon.png" alt="shop_coming_soon" title="shop_coming_soon">&lt;/a>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Team Web Building</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/team-web-building/</link><pubDate>Fri, 01 Jul 2011 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/team-web-building/</guid><description>&lt;p>Most of the websites I’ve ever worked on have been with Teams across the Globe.  The client in Europe must have his intent fulfilled.  The Web coder in California must understand some of the subtlety of design.  The artist must uphold the integrity of the design.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Here is a snippet of interaction during a web development cycle.  This is the first iteration of Grubby’s website.  The Photo Gallery was coming along nicely, but needed some extra attention, ensuring the code would reflect the initial design.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Four Oh Four Screen</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/four-oh-four-screen/</link><pubDate>Tue, 19 Apr 2011 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/four-oh-four-screen/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/Untitled-1.jpg">&lt;img src="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/Untitled-1.jpg" alt="Untitled-1" title="Untitled-1">&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>It is customary for websites to have error pages that are somewhat fun. Its frustrating when things break on the internet, so if we are hit with something that makes us smile, it is a bit easier to let go the frustration in running into a glitch.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>For FollowGrubby.com I had the idea of using the ‘King of Blades’ Critical Striking the webpage. This idea came to mind as I was thinking of the numbers involved with the error screens. I am, of course a huge fan of Warcraft 3, so when thinking of something that related to such a huge number as 404, I quickly found myself seeing Critical Strike numbers popping out of my poor Arch Mage as he would desperately seek the solace of a Holy Light, and a StormBolt to slow the blade delivered death that was sure to be his destiny.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>WIld Goose Casio Print Designs</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/wild-goose-casio-print-designs/</link><pubDate>Tue, 22 Mar 2011 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/wild-goose-casio-print-designs/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/a965d3aa5f34_F61C/casino-aniversery2.png">&lt;img src="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/a965d3aa5f34_F61C/casino-aniversery2_thumb.png" alt="casino aniversery2" title="casino aniversery2">&lt;/a>  &lt;a href="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/a965d3aa5f34_F61C/Friday-Poker-copy.png">&lt;img src="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/a965d3aa5f34_F61C/Friday-Poker-copy_thumb.png" alt="Friday Poker copy" title="Friday Poker copy">&lt;/a>   &lt;a href="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/a965d3aa5f34_F61C/holdem_tournament-copy2.png">&lt;img src="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/a965d3aa5f34_F61C/holdem_tournament-copy2_thumb.png" alt="holdem_tournament copy2" title="holdem_tournament copy2">&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>These assets were used for a Casino as a way to update some of the look and feel of their promotions and table print outs.  The project was far and away from what I usually work on.  In the end, though the project was very fun and I was able to learn many more interesting techniques in creating fun designs for print of online assets.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>TopReplays Avatars</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/esports/topreplays-avatars/</link><pubDate>Fri, 26 Feb 2010 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/esports/topreplays-avatars/</guid><description>&lt;p>Here are some avatars that I was commissioned to create for &lt;a href="http://www.topreplays.com">TopReplays.com&lt;/a> The site is awesome!&lt;/p>
